to the editor brent staples editorial observer jan 5 rightly speaks of the need for a national reading campaign discussing books movies and tv shows is the beginning of real comprehension today 's standards demand that pupils be able to respond to literature that they hear and read only a fraction of students can perform at expected levels a successful reading program must be formulated for all to learn teacher training will be only the tip of the iceberg parent education is a must having trained volunteers and teenagers available to discuss stories and books with youngsters would go a long way toward helping reading comprehension odey raviv sea cliff ny jan 7 2002 the writer is a new york city public school teacher

